Package: juicydown
Title: Convert R Markdown into HTML with Inline Styles
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Kenji", "Sato", , "kenji@kenjisato.jp", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0000-4520-2560"))
Description: A convenient tool to create HTML with inline styles. It is 
  particularly useful when working on CMS whose code editor eliminates style and
  link tags. The main use case of the package is the learning management system,
  Moodle.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
URL: https://kenjisato.github.io/juicydown/
